<H2>The Software Download Page</H2>


This page contain links to down load the Dairy Debate Stack, and The

Cover Crops Database Stack.
<H3><A NAME="DairyDebate">The Dairy Debate Stack</A></H3>
The Dairy Debate Stack considers the implications of the use of
recombinant bovine 
growth hormone (BGH) by the dairy industry, and
rotational grazing, for animal
 health, consumers, the environment, farm
economics, and rural communities.    
Its purpose is to broaden and
inform the public debate over dairy technology 
and food safety.<P>

The Dairy Debate is a stand-alone application stack for 
the Apple
Macintosh computer. It  does not require Hypercard to run. It will 
run
with either System v. 6.0.7 or System 7. It is stored here as a BinHexed,

self-extracting archive. The file is 837K.<P>

Download:  
<A HREF="ftp://www.sarep.ucdavis.edu/ftp\pub\Dairy_Debate.sea.hqx">
<IMG SRC="../../Images/Dairy.gif">Dairy_Debate.sea.hqx</A><P>


<H3><A NAME="CoverCrop">Cover Crop Database Stack</A></H3>

The UC SAREP Cover Crop Database includes over 5,000 items gleaned from
over 600 separate sources, including journal articles, conference
proceedings, standard textbooks, unpublished data, and personal
communications from researchers and farmers.  The information in the
database concerns the management and effects of more than 32 species of
plants usable as cover crops.  The database was developed with funding
from USDA's Sustainable Agriculture Research and Education program (SARE), 
the State of California's Water Resources Control Board, and the California Energy Commission.<P>

<B>Note: All of the information contained in the cover crop hypercard stack is now available online. <BR>
<A HREF="/sarep/ccrop">Checkout our Cover Crop Resource Page.</A></B>
<P>

<STRONG>This is a prototype (beta) version</STRONG> developed by  UC SAREP for 
Apple
Macintosh computers.  This version of the program is available as a
standalone 
application or as a hypercard stack. Only the Hypercard stack
requires Hypercard 
2.2 or Hypercard Player 2.2 in order to work properly.

The BinHexed, 
self-extracting archive of the stand-alone is
2,421K.<BR>
The BinHexed, 
self-extracting archive of the Hypercard Stack is
1,800K.<P>



